<s docid="AP890615-0263" num="7" wdcount="27"> Wal-Mart founder Sam Walton pitched in 
to help check-out clerks at his store in this Florida Panhandle city when an 
electronic glitch shut down the cash registers.</s>

<s docid="AP890323-0234" num="15" wdcount="22"> His example is followed by other Wal-
Mart executives and most make a point of spending a lot of time in the field.</s>

<s docid="FT922-14265" num="8" wdcount="28"> By 1991 the chain's sales had risen to 
nearly Dollars 44bn, making it the world's largest retailer in terms of 
